<title>ITALY: Italy offers 12 trln lire of BOTs for sale.</title>
<headline>Italy offers 12 trln lire of BOTs for sale.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian Treasury said it was</p>
<p>offering 12.00 trillion lire of short term bills (BOT),</p>
<p>replacing 13.75 trillion lire of expiring paper.</p>
<p>A Treasury statement said it would offer:</p>
<p>*3.25 trillion lire of three-month BOTs</p>
<p>*4.25 trillion lire of six-month paper</p>
<p>*4.50 trillion lire of one-year bills.</p>
<p>Subscriptions close at 1200 GMT on December 10.</p>
<p>The Treasury added that it would offer 2.5 trillion lire of two-year zero couponed certificates (CTZ) with subscriptions for that sale also closing at 1200 GMT, December 10.</p>
